{
  "texts": [
    "However, scholarly opinion suggests that ChatGPT is not a substitute for teacher-student interaction, but rather a means of supporting it (Dwivedi et al., 2023; Gašević et al., 2023; O'Leary, 2023).",
    "While ChatGPT is a valuable tool to enhance educational opportunities, caution should be exercised when using it (Tlili et al., 2023).",
    "The training data used for ChatGPT could be inaccurate or incomplete, making it possible for ChatGPT to produce erroneous answers (Lancaster, 2023).",
    "Therefore, individuals who wish to use this tool for domain-specific research should possess sufficient expertise to verify its outputs (Qureshi et al., 2023).",
    "Therefore, teachers and students ought to investigate ways to utilize it efficiently while acknowledging its constraints (Lancaster, 2023)."
  ]
}